Six people, yesterday, died, while one sustained injury in an auto crash that occurred around Kara turning along the Lagos-Ibadan Expressway corridor of Ogun State
    
The crash involved a Toyota car marked LRG165AA, when the driver lost control of the vehicle due to excessive speed.
 
Spokesperson for the Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), in the state, Superintendent Florence Okpe, confirmed the incident to newsmen in Abeokuta
  
Okpe said out of the eight occupants (six female and two male), only one person survived with injury, while the rest died on the spot.  